Step 1: Create an Amazon S3 Bucket and Organize Data into Folders
  Sign in to AWS Console
  Open Amazon S3 Service
  Create a Bucket
  Create Folders (Prefixes)
Step 2: Configure Access Permissions for Secure Data Storage
  Access Control Lists (ACLs)
  Bucket Policies
      {
  "Version": "2012-10-17",
  "Statement": [
    {
      "Effect": "Allow",
      "Principal": "*",
      "Action": "s3:GetObject",
      "Resource": "arn:aws:s3:::project-2-zaffar/*"
      }
    ]
  }

  IAM Roles and User Permissions
Step 3: Implement Data Backup and Versioning
  Versioning
  Cross-Region Replication (CRR)
{
  <CORSConfiguration>
    <CORSRule>
      <AllowedOrigin>https://example.com</AllowedOrigin>
      <AllowedMethod>GET</AllowedMethod>
      <MaxAgeSeconds>3000</MaxAgeSeconds>
      <AllowedHeader>*</AllowedHeader>
    </CORSRule>
  </CORSConfiguration>
  }
 }
}

